headline: Has KeyCorp’s Recent 28% Rally Already Priced In Its Rebound Prospects for 2025?
summary: If you are wondering whether KeyCorp at around $20.94 is still a smart buy after its run up, or if you are late to the party, this breakdown will help you decide whether the current price makes sense. The stock has quietly put together a strong stretch, up 1.4% over the last week, 20.7% over the past month, 23.3% year to date, and 28.4% over the last year, with a 64.5% gain over five years that is starting to turn more heads. headline: Reassessing KeyCorp (KEY): Is the Recent Momentum Justified by Its Valuation?
summary: KeyCorp (KEY) has quietly rewarded patient shareholders, with the stock up around 21% over the past month and nearly 10% in the past 3 months, outpacing many regional bank peers.
